<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-269] Berkeley (persistent) agent for FlumeAppender does not work if batch size is 1 (the default)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-269</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Repro steps:&lt;br/&gt;
Use persistent agent from the FlumeAppender while the succeeding Flume agent is down.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected result:&lt;br/&gt;
Logs should queue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actual result:&lt;br/&gt;
2013-05-28 17:02:12,921 ERROR Unable to delete event java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException: A transacti&lt;br/&gt;
on was not supplied when opening this cursor: delete&lt;br/&gt;
        at com.sleepycat.je.Cursor.checkUpdatesAllowed(Cursor.java:4007)&lt;br/&gt;
        at com.sleepycat.je.Cursor.delete(Cursor.java:689)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.logging.log4j.flume.appender.FlumePersistentManager$WriterThread.run(FlumePersisten&lt;br/&gt;
tManager.java:448)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround:&lt;br/&gt;
Set the batchSize to a number &amp;gt; 1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
